text: â€œYoung people want to be part of how theyâ€™re governed and I believe they will have a say in their future and create opportunities for themselves. The youth will be a key component in how the Middle East emerges in the next decade.â€ - Sunil John. #BakerMiddleEast
"Two in five young Arabs have considered emigrating according to the #ArabYouthSurvey 2020, citing lack of opportunities and government corruption in their own countries."  #BakerMiddleEast

"Young Arabs view tackling government corruption and creating new job opportunities as the top issues that must be dealt with in the next 10 years, in order for the region to move forward." #BakerMiddleEast

"We began the Arab Youth Survey in 2008 when the region was data poor. In 2011, after the Arab Spring, everyone started looking at our survey to help understand the region" Sunil John. #BakerMiddleEast

"The Arab region is the youngest region in the world - if you want to understand the region, you must understand the hearts and minds of its young people." @asdaabcw  Founder Sunil John. #BakerMiddleEast
